      "writtenOn": "2020-12-09T17:27:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i feel like this might be excessive.\nmost of the time 1 test result correspond to 3 test variants, so it is likely that we would be fetching 3x more data than needed.\n\nalso this still doesn\u0027t guarantee that we will fetch PageSize of test variants.\n\nI assume you do this in order to decide whether to compute page token.\nI think we can be more precise by counting the number of rows Spanner returns, rather than counting the number of test variants we return.\nFor example, if we requested N test results from Spanner, but it returned N-1, then there should be next_page_token.\nIf we have discarded `current` test variant (see another comment) because it didn\u0027t fit PageSize, then there should be next_page_token.\n\n\nWith that, we can be more efficient with a factor closer to 1.0 here",
      "range": {
