      "message": "nit: \n\n1) L318-321 is same as L326-329\n2) allocated slice in L310 is thrown away in L325\n\nwhy not\n\n  var tvs ]*uipb.TestVariant\n\n  // Fetch test variants with unexpected results.\n  if q.unexpected {\n    // TODO(crbug.com/1112127): populate next page token.\n    tvs \u003d make([]*uipb.TestVariant, 0, q.PageSize)\n    err \u003d q.queryTestVariantsWithUnexpectedResults(ctx, func(tv *uipb.TestVariant) error {\n      tvs \u003d append(tvs, tv)\n      return nil\n    })\n  } else {\n    tvs, err \u003d q.fetchTestVariantsWithOnlyExpectedResults(ctx)\n  }\n  if err !\u003d nil {\n    tvs \u003d nil\n  }\n  return\n\nalso, code would be even nicer if it was `if q.expected` because `else` would be closer to `if`.\nand also because it would use positive `expected` (as opposed to negative unexpected)",
